ALL INTEREST RATE SWAP AGREEMENTS MEET THE SHORTCUT METHOD REQUIREMENTS UNDER THE ACCOUNTING STANDARDS FOR DERIVATIVES AND HEDGING. ACCORDINGLY, CHANGES IN THE FAIR VALUES OF

THE INTEREST RATE SWAP AGREEMENTS ARE CONSIDERED TO EXACTLY OFFSET CHANGES IN THE FAIR VALUE OF THE UNDERLYING LONG-TERM DEBT. REFER TO FAIR VALUE HEDGES IN THIS NOTE FOR ADDITIONAL DETAIL.

